import React, { Component } from 'react' import { Timeline, TimelineItem } from 'vertical-timeline-component-for-react'; import Mar122020 from './experiences/Mar122020' import Jan021994 from './experiences/Jan021994' export default class Experience extends Component { render(){ return(
Before you go down the rabbit hole of my life, it's important that I tell you why it's organized the way it is.
I think of life as composed of a few different sections.
  • Personal
  • -- relationships (family, friendships, romantic)
  • -- finances
  • -- health
  • -- spiritulality (meditation)
  • Education
  • Business (Career and Work)
  • Athletics
  • Volunteering/Community service
  • Arts
Thinking of my life allows me to better myself in every area. Can you be split it further?
Sure, but for me, there's almost no reason to. I can look at this, see how much time I spend on each of them, and decide if I have my priorities straight or not.

Events will be composed of:
  • Title
  • Subtitle
  • Date entered
  • Date finished
  • Location
  • Company etc involved
  • what did i actually do?
  • ideally an image?
  • Link to github or paper or whatever that may have
  • Tags (e.g. personal project, work, school, award (star?)
  • skills learned?
  • blogs associated?
) } }
